{"TopicId":215982,"ForumId":120,"TopicTitle":"Ships spawn under VAB after reverting to VAB","CreatedByName":"Eli Phillips","CreatedById":227767,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-27T13:54:10Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Eli Phillips","CreatedById":227767,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-27T13:54:10Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI have come across this so many times and it has spoiled my playtime in ksp2\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat happens is when reverting to \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003EVAB\u003C/abbr\u003E sometimes your ship separates itself into separate parts and spawns under the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003EVAB\u003C/abbr\u003E, but now you may think \u0022oh then just bring the pieces up and put it back together\u0022, You can\u0027t, The pieces lose their connection points and you can\u0027t put it back together so I just have had to rebuild my ship.\u00A0 Another thing is when you zoom in too close to the ship while it is under the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003EVAB\u003C/abbr\u003E it completely leaves the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003EVAB\u003C/abbr\u003E entirely and your camera gets stuck. One last thing is that this can also sometimes happen when just loading a ship in the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003EVAB\u003C/abbr\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAll in all I am happy to be a part of the process to make ksp2 as good as its predecessor.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Spicat","CreatedById":228085,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-27T14:33:44Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAre you talking about this bug?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022113\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/3TmC6QUFzCo?start=57\u0026amp;feature=oembed\u0022 title=\